Maze

Class Cell

  • java.lang.Object
    • Maze.Cell

  • public class Cell
extends java.lang.Object
    Cell class which describes a cell object that contains a north, east, south, and west wall as well as information that describes whether it is a cell that is visible, visited, or it's type (border, time point, end point, etc...).

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      private boolean border
      Boolean flag which represents whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object is a border cell or not.
      private int cellNumber
      Represents the cell number based on the dimensions of the maze (i.e., 2 by 2 maze has 1 to 4 cell numbers).
      private int coordX
      Represents the physical x coordinate of this cell object on the maze (Graphical maze).
      private int coordY
      Represents the physical y coordinate of this cell object on the maze (Graphical maze).
      private boolean eastWall
      Boolean which represents whether a hypothetical/conceptual east wall exists for this cell object.
      private boolean endPoint
      Boolean flag which describes the whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object is a end point.
      private boolean northWall
      Boolean which represents whether a hypothetical/conceptual north wall exists for this cell object.
      private int positionX
      Represents the row value of this cell object.
      private int positionY
      Represents the column value of this cell object.
      private boolean southWall
      Boolean which represents whether a hypothetical/conceptual south wall exists for this cell object.
      private boolean startPoint
      Boolean flag which describes the whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object is a start point.
      private boolean timePoint
      Boolean flag which describes the whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object is a time point.
      private boolean visibile
      Boolean flag which represents whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object is a visible cell or not, if it is invisible then it will not be drawn to the screen.
      private boolean visitedFlag
      Boolean flag which represents whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object has been "visited" or not.
      private boolean westWall
      Boolean which represents whether a hypothetical/conceptual west wall exists for this cell object.

        private boolean timePoint
        Boolean flag which describes the whether this hypothetical/conceptual cell object is a time point. The object can either be a normal cell (tile), a time point, end point or start point.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Cell

        public Cell(int cNum)
        Initializes this cell object where each wall in the cell is existent. thus a completely closed cell is created. The cell is initially visible, unvisited and does not have a specific cell type (time point, end point, etc...).
        Parameters:
        cNum - Cell number assigned by GenMaze, dependent on the maze (grid) size.
